Shorty's is consistently delicious no matter how many times I've been there, and no matter what time of day I visit (and I've been there late!). They have a good happy hour with $5 beers. It gets packed between 5 and 7, but the servers do a good job making sure everyone gets attention. You can't go wrong with any sandwich, but if its your first time, I highly recommend the buffalo chicken cheese steak. I've had more than 30 of them over the past few years, if that says anything. If you're feeling lazy, their delivery is generally always on time and the fries somehow always arrive fresh and crispy, which always impressed me.

It's an ok place, a watering hall in all but a name. The four of us stopped by for an office lunch around 1pm on a Thursday. The wait wasn't long, less than 5 minutes, the music was a bit extra loud and people yelling over it to hear each other didn't help the situation. We ordered mozzarella triangles which were very good and marinara was perfectly sweet and tangy. Appetizers and sandwiches were brought together, which in my case, was great, because mine was so large I needed a knife to cut it but we weren't given any utensils at all because we didn't order anything that could technically be eaten with one. I had to wait about 5 minutes till the waitress came to take out neighbors order to ask for utensils, but was only given a fork, which I then ended up using. The sandwich was really good and very large though. My coworker enjoyed her wings which were perfectly spicy and, again, portion was large enough to save some for the next day. My other coworker had a chicken cutlet special. He asked for mushrooms and onions, but neither were on his sandwich when it was brought. The waitress brought him some on the side when bringing my fork, but he said that he didn't taste any mushrooms, only onions and peppers. Overall ok food and somewhat rushed service.
